research_municipality_step.notes: Balch Springs, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government, which is a type of mayor-council system. The City Council consists of a Mayor and six Council Members. The Mayor and one Council Member (Place 2) are elected at-large, while the other five Council Members are elected from single-member districts. The City Council appoints a City Manager to handle day-to-day operations. Elishima Myles also holds the role of Mayor Pro Tem.
